The paper focuses on reinforcement learning algorithms for robot controllers, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of prior knowledge and data-driven models, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of simulators and dynamics, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these algorithms to humanoid robots, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for perception.
